<dl id="n12152f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12152f">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12152f"> 152(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> mysterious / mendacious / shrewd (Pel) / incredibly loquacious </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: A line joins &lsquo;incredibly&rsquo; and &lsquo;C&aelig;lestius&rsquo; above. </mm> <blockquote class="sources">St. Augustine, while charging Pelagius with mysteriousness, mendacity, and shrewdness, calls C&aelig;lestius &hellip; &ldquo;incredibly loquacious&rdquo; <small> <a name="CEPEL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CEPEL"><cite title="source">&ldquo;Pelagius&rdquo;</cite></a> <cite a>Catholic Encyclopaedia</cite></a> (1911) 605a</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
